Get similiarities between mental models of users

Source: R/similarity.R
get_model_sims.Rd

This function calculates the similarity between the mental models of of users, either among all users or among groups of users.

Usage

get_model_sims(mentalmodel, method = NULL, group_var = NULL, output = "matrix")

Arguments

mentalmodel

A mtoolr object with models from multiple users (therefore not an aggregated object)

method

The method to calculate similarity between mental models of users. At the moment, this defaults to "gower". Other options are "simple_overlap" and "jaccard".

group_var

A character string giving the name of a (preferably factor) variable in the user data to create groups of users. For each group of users, a similarity matrix is calculated. All matrices are returned in a list.

output

Either "matrix" or "tibble". If "matrix, a similarity matrix is returned. If "tibble" a tibble dataframe of pairs of users with similarities is returned. Defaults to "matrix"

Value

If no group_var is supplied a similarity matrix or tibble, depending on output chosen. If a group_var is supplied a list of similarity matrices for each level of the grouping variable.
